3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Hyperliquid calculates MEME/USDT funding rates every hour based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices, with payments occurring at the top of each hour. The platform's on-chain order book ensures transparent price discovery, while the L1 infrastructure enables real-time funding rate updates. Unlike 8-hour CEX cycles, the hourly intervals create more frequent arbitrage windows but require active position management."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","MEME","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEME tokens typically exhibit high volatility and sentiment-driven price movements, creating significant funding rate disparities across exchanges. The smaller trading volume on Hyperliquid compared to major CEXs can lead to sustained funding rate premiums, especially during meme coin hype cycles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical MEME Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEME perpetuals on Hyperliquid have shown distinct funding rate patterns during different market phases. During meme coin rallies, funding rates often turn significantly positive as traders rush to long positions, creating opportunities for short-side arbitrage. The 1-hour intervals mean these elevated rates compound more frequently than traditional 8-hour cycles. Conversely, during bearish sentiment, negative funding rates can persist for extended periods, benefiting long position holders. The on-chain nature means all historical data is verifiable and accessible for backtesting strategies."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Cross-Exchange Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEME funding rates on Hyperliquid often diverge from CEXs like Binance and OKX due to different user bases and liquidity profiles. DEX users may hold positions longer due to lower gas costs for maintaining positions versus frequent trading. This creates opportunities to capture funding rate differentials by holding opposite positions across venues. The key advantage is Hyperliquid's permissionless access, allowing arbitrageurs to scale positions without KYC limits. However, the USDC-only settlement requires managing stablecoin exposure when arbitraging against USDT-settled venues."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management for MEME Arbitrage"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"MEME token arbitrage carries elevated risks due to extreme price volatility and potential liquidity gaps during rapid moves. Position sizing must account for the possibility of funding rates flipping quickly as sentiment changes. The smaller market size means large positions can impact local funding rates, reducing arbitrage efficiency. Smart contract risk exists despite Hyperliquid's security focus, requiring position limits and monitoring. Additionally, the correlation between MEME price movements and funding rates can create scenarios where arbitrage profits are offset by directional exposure."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often do MEME/USDT funding payments occur on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Funding payments occur every hour at the top of the hour on Hyperliquid, providing 24 payment opportunities per day. This is significantly more frequent than the standard 8-hour cycles on most CEXs, creating more granular arbitrage opportunities."},{"question":"What makes MEME funding rates different on Hyperliquid versus CEXs?","answer":"Hyperliquid's on-chain order book and different user base often lead to funding rate divergences from CEXs. The permissionless nature and 1-hour cycles can create sustained rate differentials, especially during meme coin volatility spikes."},{"question":"Can I arbitrage MEME funding rates without holding the underlying token?","answer":"Yes, you can capture funding rate differentials through delta-neutral positions across exchanges without directional exposure to MEME price movements. This involves holding opposite positions on different venues to collect funding rate spreads."},{"question":"What are the main risks of MEME funding rate arbitrage on Hyperliquid?","answer":"Key risks include extreme MEME price volatility that can overwhelm funding profits, liquidity gaps during rapid moves, and smart contract risks inherent to DeFi protocols. The smaller market size also means position impact on local rates."}]}]
